 <div class="on-this-page">
<p>The Transport for London (TfL) Board recently agreed to the freezing of all taxi and private hire licence fees with driver licensing fees being frozen for a second year running. </p>
<p>The Board also approved two changes to taxi and private hire fees which will come into effect today.</p>
<p>Taxi and private hire licence fees are reviewed annually and all funds generated are used to cover licensing and administrative costs.&nbsp; </p>
<p>The taxi and private hire driver, operator and vehicle licence fees remain frozen at 2010/11 levels however, there will be increases in both the Knowledge of London appearance and written test fees. </p>
<p>These changes continue to reflect the cost of administering the Knowledge of London examination process including the back office administration activity, managing the written test and the knowledge appearances themselves.&nbsp; </p>
<p>The current and revised Knowledge of London fees are provided in the table below:</p>
<p>
