<td><strong>&nbsp;2010/11 fee (&pound;)</strong></td></tr>
<tr>
<td>&nbsp;Knowledge appearance - taxi driver applicants </td>
<td>&nbsp;200</td>
<td>&nbsp;250</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>&nbsp;Knowledge written test - taxi driver applicants </td>
<td>&nbsp;50</td>
<td>&nbsp;100</td></tr></tbody></table></div></p>
<p>John Mason, TfL's Director of Taxi and Private Hire, said: 'We have taken into account the difficult economic conditions drivers are facing and, combined with the back office cost savings we are striving to make, have been able to freeze the majority of fees this year.&nbsp; </p>
<p>'The increases to the Knowledge of London fees reflect the cost of administering this process and therefore not passing these costs on to other licensees.'</p>
